Dear all,=0A=
=0A=
This is the second and last annoucement for the Young Topologists' Meeting =
2015 that will take place on July 6-10, 2015 at the EPFL in Lausanne, Switz=
erland.=0A=
=0A=
The goal is to bring together graduate students, recent PhDs and young rese=
archers to give talks concerning their own work. In addition, there will be=
  two mini-courses:=0A=
=0A=
Emily Riehl (Harvard University): Infinity category theory from scratch,=0A=
Gunnar Carlsson (Stanford University): Methods of applied topology.=0A=
=0A=
The registration deadline is 30th April 2015. =0A=
The deadline to apply for funding is 28th February 2015.=0A=
=0A=
We can provide accommodation for about 70 participants.=0A=
Moreover, we applied for a NSF grant in order to fund about 20 participants=
  from American universities.=0A=
A full application, including recommendation letters and a CV, will be  req=
uested upon positive answer from the NSF.=0A=
We encourage women and under-represented minorities to apply.=0A=
=0A=
The registration form and further information can be found on http://gr-he.=
epfl.ch/ytm2015 .=0A=
=0A=
We hope to see you this summer in Switzerland!=0A=
=0A=
The organizers,=0A=
=0A=
Rachel Jeitziner,=0A=
Martina Rovelli,=0A=
Kay Werndli,=0A=
Dimitri Zaganidis.=0A=


